resources.string: \nAndoidTracker is a science aggregation app that displays information about Near Earth Objects.

What Is A Near-Earth Object (NEO)? \nNear-Earth Objects (NEOs) are comets and asteroids that have been nudged by the gravitational attraction of nearby planets into orbits that allow them to enter the Earth\'s neighborhood. Composed mostly of water ice with embedded dust particles...
All the data is from the NASA Near Earth Object program\nhttp://neo.jpl.nasa.gov.
NASA NEO - Impact Risk - Sentry Risk Table\nhttp://neo.jpl.nasa.gov/risk/
NASA NEO - The Torino Impact Hazard Scale \nhttp://neo.jpl.nasa.gov/torino_scale.html
